You're missing the **`BindingContext`**. Your bindings are correct, but the page doesn't know *which object* to bind to.

**Fix — set `BindingContext` in your code-behind:**

```csharp
public partial class MyPage : ContentPage
{
    public MyPage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = new MyViewModel();
    }
}
```

**Also ensure your ViewModel implements `INotifyPropertyChanged`** so the UI updates when properties change:

```csharp
public class MyViewModel : INotifyPropertyChanged
{
    public event PropertyChangedEventHandler PropertyChanged;

    private string _title;
    public string Title
    {
        get => _title;
        set { _title = value; PropertyChanged?.Invoke(this, new PropertyChangedEventArgs(nameof(Title))); }
    }
    // same pattern for Description
}
```

**Alternatively**, if you use the MVVM Community Toolkit, you can simplify with `ObservableObject` + `[ObservableProperty]`:

```csharp
public partial class MyViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _title;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _description;
}
```
